-- Dubai's Landmark to Spend $1 Billion on Acquisitions in 2011, Arabian Says
-- B y   S h a j i   M a t h e w
-- 2010-10-17T06:36:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-17/dubai-s-landmark-to-spend-1-billion-on-acquisitions-in-2011-arabian-says.html
Landmark Group, a Dubai-based
retailer with stakes in companies including Debenhams Plc, plans
to spend $1 billion next year on acquisitions, Chairman Micky
Jagtiani was cited as saying by Arabian Business.  Landmark prefers buying businesses in the U.K. and in the
hospitality and retail industry, he told Arabian Business. The
company is studying the New Look Group Plc fashion brand, he
said without giving further details.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
